skos:Concept.skos:scopeNote: {"id": "67fcd517-2b14-45a6-abf6-a29e4d7ba040", "value": "That portion of the Pacific which stretches from the Arctic Ocean in the north to the equator."}
{"id": "705540d4-7115-4489-8387-c750dad8406a", "value": "That portion of the Pacific which stretches from the equator to Antarctica."}

{"id": "be41c76b-8c6f-4f14-9a3c-b6653b9d7145", "value": "Bordering the five continents of Antarctica, Asia, Australasia, North and South America, the Pacific is the largest of the world's oceans, and covers more area (63,838,000 square miles) than that of the combined seven continents."}
{"id": "1d68e5a6-af2a-402e-ab4e-dbd77ce32bdb", "value": "A sea within a sea, the Arabian Sea consists of the northern part of the Indian Ocean bordered by India, Pakistan, Iran, Oman and Yemen."}

{"id": "12aae577-9f98-447e-ab3b-4fe93ef55b67", "value": "The ocean which surrounds the continent of Antarctica, and includes the most southerly regions of the three largest oceans, the Pacific, Atlantic and Indian."}

{"id": "7c45ce2b-b586-475d-82c0-6322309f41a0", "value": "Bordered by the continents of Africa, Asia and Europe, the Mediterranean covers some 967,000 sq miles. It is linked to the Atlantic Ocean by the Straits of Gibraltar."}
{"id": "44538804-a04d-49ed-bb6b-97d5883f3bcb", "value": "A sea within a sea, the Adriatic consists of that part of the Mediterranean which separates Italy from the Balkans and Greece."}

{"id": "a71a7b52-9d89-4847-b1e2-e3dca18cb15b", "value": "Bordering the continents of Africa, Antarctica, Asia and Australasia, the Indian Ocean covers 28,364,000 square miles."}

{"id": "082f3fb2-4129-4aba-a021-af3392100508", "value": "Bordering the continents of Asia, Europe and North America the Arctic Ocean covers 5,426,000 square miles. Situated over the North Pole, much of the ocean remains frozen year round."}
